<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Installation - Lower Crankcase Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s15.4.5" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Lower Crankcase Assembly</title>
        <para>With acceptable bearing clearance as determined in
            <hotlnk document="eges3451_313.xml" xrefid="s15.3.3.ref1">Main Bearing Fit Check</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="s15.3.3.ref1"/>, install lower crankcase assembly as follows:
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When inserting main bearings, make sure oil is not between back side of bearing and lower
                    crankcase assembly bearing saddles.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place crankshaft lower main bearings in lower crankcase assembly. Make sure locking tabs on
                bearings are snapped in saddle.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new lower crankcase assembly seals.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply clean engine oil to lower bearing inserts, crankshaft journals, and main bearing
                bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015031" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07105.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Main bearing bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M14 x 127 main bearing bolt (10)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M14 x 114 main bearing bolt (10)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, install new bolts for lower crankcase assembly if lower crankcase
                    assembly is serviced.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, install longer main cap bolts (M14 x 127) inboard and shorter main cap
                    bolts (M14 x 114) outboard.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 10 new M14&#160;x&#160;127 main bearing bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 10 new M14&#160;x&#160;114 main bearing bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015032" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07115.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Torque sequence for main bearing bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten bolts using above sequence as follows:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Tighten bolts to 149 N&#183;m (110 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Tighten bolts to 176 N&#183;m (130 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Tighten bolts to 231 N&#183;m (170 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015033" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07102.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft assembly gear backlash check (camshaft gear to crankshaft gear)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial indicator with magnetic base</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft gear</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Confirm that camshaft gear backlash is within specifications.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Crankshaft gear must be fixed and not allowed to rotate; the camshaft gear must rotate, for a
                    correct reading.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check and record backlash for camshaft gear-to-crankshaft gear as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">dial indicator with magnetic base</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t3"/>
                    on rear of engine.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position dial indicator tip on a gear tooth and remove lash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Rotate gear by hand and read indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If backlash exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_323.xml" xrefid="s15.t1">specified limits</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t1"/>, replace camshaft assembly.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015034" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft end play</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check crankshaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount dial indicator on lower crankcase assembly with indicator tip on end of crankshaft
                    gear as shown.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Move crankshaft forward with pry bar and zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Move crankshaft back and forth while reading dial indicator. Compare dial indicator
                    reading with
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_323.xml" xrefid="s15.t1">specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t1"/>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If end play exceeds specified limits, replace upper thrust bearing.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
